    job_description:
      "Title: Developer Premium II - Collibra Data Engineer/Collibra Developer\n\nLocation: Washington, DC 20433\n\nDuration: 6 Months – Long Term Contract\n\nHybrid Onsite: 4 days per week from Day 1, with a full transition to 100% onsite anticipated soon.\n\nJob Summary:\n\nWe are seeking a Collibra Data Engineer/Collibra Developer with hands-on experience in configuring and customizing the Collibra platform to meet specific business needs and data governance requirements. Enterprise implementation is essential; finance domain is preferred.\n\nAbout the Role:\n\nThis role is critical to supporting and scaling our metadata management capabilities using Collibra within an Azure environment. You will be part of a growing team responsible for enabling robust data governance practices, frameworks, and tools across the enterprise. The ideal candidate will be someone who can hit the ground running with a solid understanding of Collibra principles and implementation in cloud environments.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Act as a key contributor in the implementation and maintenance of metadata management and data governance frameworks using Collibra.\n• Collaborate with internal stakeholders and clients to gather requirements and deliver governance solutions.\n• Support enterprise initiatives around data access, classification, and control using governance frameworks.\n• Leverage Collibra in combination with Azure-native tools to support governance-related use cases.\n• Partner with cross-functional teams to ensure best practices are followed across data governance initiatives.\n• Provide client-facing technical guidance as needed.\n\nRequired Qualifications:\n• 8+ years of overall experience in data engineering or data management roles.\n• 2-3 years of hands-on experience with Collibra in a professional setting.\n• Proven understanding of Collibra principles, architecture, and implementation.\n• Strong experience in data governance as a domain, particularly around metadata management and data access policies.\n• Cloud experience: Azure preferred, but AWS acceptable.\n• Ability to work independently and contribute from day one.\n\nPreferred Qualifications:\n• Experience working within financial services or other highly regulated industries.\n• Familiarity with Unity Catalog, broader Azure stack, or other governance tools.\n• Demonstrated ability to interface with business stakeholders and clients.\n• Strong communication and stakeholder engagement skills.\n• Prior experience with COTS products supporting data governance functions.\n\n“Mindlance is an Equal Opportunity Employer and does not discriminate in employment on the basis of – Minority/Gender/Disability/Religion/LGBTQI/Age/Veterans.”",
