      "About TTC\nThe Testing Consultancy (TTC) is a global specialist software quality and technology solutions company, helping organizations transform the way they deliver business outcomes. We partner with clients to improve processes, streamline operations, and enhance decision-making through effective analysis, strategy, and solution implementation.\n\nPosition Summary\n\nWe are seeking an experienced UiPath Test Automation Senior Consultant to join our team. The ideal candidate will bring strong test automation expertise, proven software development experience, and prior exposure to UiPath. Due to the nature of the work, SECRET or TOP SECRET clearance is required for system access.\n\nPerks of Working for TTC\n• Competitive Base Salary\n• Medical, Dental, Vision Benefits\n• 401(k) with Company Match\n• Paid Time Off\n• Paid Holidays\n• Work-Life Balance\n• Relaxed Work Environment\n• Growth and Development Opportunities\n\nResponsibilities\n• Design, develop, and implement UiPath Test Automations test cases.\n• Collaborate with project stakeholders to understand testing needs and translate them into automation solutions.\n• Develop, execute, and maintain automated test scripts to ensure functionality, performance, and security compliance.\n• Conduct thorough reviews of automation code for accuracy, efficiency, and maintainability.\n• Partner with software engineers, QA teams, and business analysts to ensure alignment with project goals.\n• Document automation processes and provide knowledge transfer to project stakeholders.\n\nRole Requirements\n• 2+ years of UiPath experience (Core RPA required; Document Understanding or Test Products preferred).\n• 2+ years of Test Automation experience.\n• 5+ years of software development experience.\n• Active SECRET or TOP SECRET clearance (required for system access).\n• Strong problem-solving skills and ability to work independently in a remote environment.\n• Excellent communication and collaboration skills.\n\nQualifications\n• Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or related field (or equivalent experience).\n• Demonstrated expertise in UiPath automation solutions.\n• Solid background in software development and QA methodologies.\n• Clearance: Active SECRET or TOP SECRET required.\n\nAt TTC Global, we understand the importance of diversity and the value it brings to our team. Diversity fuels creativity and fosters new perspectives, which is why we encourage all qualified candidates to apply.",
